title: Netanyahu: ‘We have killed thousands of terrorists’
description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu lauded military progress inside Gaza, warned Hezbollah against further involvement, and thanked President Biden for U.S. support.

title: In tensions over Israel-Hamas war, college campuses confront violent threats
description: As tensions surrounding the Israel-Hamas war and Gaza crisis run high, universities are scrambling to manage violent threats against staff members and students.

title: Suspect 'cooperative' in homicide investigation of California man who died after fall at dueling protests
description: A suspect in the confrontation that led to the death of a Jewish man who was injured during dueling Israeli and Palestinian rallies in California has been “cooperative,” was briefly detained and called 911 to seek medical help for the victim, officials said Tuesday.

title: Iran-linked organizations attack U.S. targets in the Middle East
description: At least 45 U.S. service members may have been injured in Iran-linked attacks on U.S. targets in Iraq and Syria. NBC News’ Courtney Kube reports on the rising tension in the Middle East.

title: 4 men charged in theft of satirical golden toilet titled ‘America,’ at Churchill’s birthplace
description: Four men were charged Monday over the theft of an 18-carat gold toilet from Blenheim Palace, where British wartime leader Winston Churchill was born.

title: Rescuers scramble to pull survivors from flattened buildings in southern Gaza's Khan Younis
description: First responders dug with their bare hands to pull victims and survivors from the debris of buildings in Khan Younis, southern Gaza, which were flattened by a huge explosion on Monday.

title: Vigils held in Jerusalem and Tel Aviv for victims of Oct. 7 Hamas attacks
description: Some 1,400 candles were lit at Jerusalem's Western Wall on Monday in tribute to the 1,400 victims of the Hamas-led terrorist attacks of Oct. 7. In Tel Aviv another vigil took place in Habima Square, where tempty beds were presented in memory of hostages who remain held in the Gaza Strip.

title: Colombian president orders recovery of $20 billion shipwreck treasure
description: The president of Colombia is calling for an accelerated recovery of the 300-year-old wreck of the ship San Jose that may hold a $20 billion stash of treasure, but an American company says half of that loot is theirs.

title: Inside Israel’s mission to destroy Hamas tunnels in Gaza
description: The Israeli army is trying to find and destroy Hamas tunnels which the terror group is using to mount ambushes. NBC News’ Raf Sanchez was given rare access inside Gaza and followed a unit of Israeli combat engineers tasked with destroying the tunnels.

title: Israeli troops expected to enter Gaza City soon
description: Israeli tanks and troops have encircled Gaza City and are expected to enter the urban area soon. The Hamas-run health ministry in Gaza says the death toll has passed 10,000. That figure could rise dramatically as troops advance. Secretary Blinken is pushing Israel to pause but there are no signs of stopping. NBC News’ Richard Engel reports.
